com.socrata.model.importer

Class DatasetInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.socrata.model.importer.DatasetInfo
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Dataset, ExternalDataset, NonDataFileDataset

    public class DatasetInfo
extends Object
    Class that contains all the information about a dataset NOT related to its actual schema. An easy way to think of this class is all the parts of a dataset you can change without having to put it into a Working Copy.

      • getResourceName

        public String getResourceName()
        Gets the resource name for this dataset. The Resource Name is a name that can be used on the URL to access the dataset. E.g. if a dataset had a resource name of my_dataset, it would be accessible via: https://mysite.socrata.com/id/my_dataset
        Returns:
        the resource name

      • getExternalId

        public String getExternalId()
        Sometimes datasets have an ID in a system outside Socrata. This field is where you can store this info. Although this is opaque to the system, common values here are URLs, URIs, GUIDs or other globally unique constructs.
        Returns:
        the external ID

      • setExternalId

        Parameters:
        externalId - the external ID

      • getId

        public String getId()
        This unique ID for this dataset. The format of this key will be the 4x4 format used by socrata, e.g. abcd-efgh This key cannot be changed after the dataset is created.
        Returns:
        the unique Id of the dataset, or null if this is not persisted yet.

      • setupLicense

        public void setupLicense(LicenseInfo licenseInfo,
                String attribution,
                String attributionLink)
        Sets up the license portion of the dataset info from a LicenseInfo and an attribution. This is a convenience method to make sure all parts of the object are set correctly and in sync.
        Parameters:
        licenseInfo - the license info about this dataset's license
        attribution - the attribution for this license. This is required when licenseInfo.attributionRequired is true
        attributionLink - a link for the attribution for this license. This is recommended when licenseInfo.attributionRequired is true

      • getRowsUpdatedAt

        public Long getRowsUpdatedAt()
        A long representing the seconds since the epoch till this was modified. NOTE: THis is seconds since the epoch, not millis. So turning into a standard Date requires multiplying by 1000.
        Returns:
        A long representing the seconds since the epoch till this was modified.

      • getGrants

        public List<Grant> getGrants()
        Gets all the permission grants for this dataset. This will include a grant to make the dataset public, or any explicit sharing with another user. May be null if there are no grants. This state is teh same as a dataset being private.
        Returns:
        list of grants

      • setGrants

        public void setGrants(List<Grant> grants)
        Sets all the permission grants for this dataset. This is an accessor on this class, but to actually make a dataset public or private, you should use the makePublic and makePrivate methods in SodaWorkflow
